Attested since the 1680s (also spelled {{m|en|jibe}} and ''gybe''), perhaps from {{der|en|nl|gijben}} (a variant of {{m|nl|gijpen||to turn sails suddenly}}, whence certainly the form {{m|en|jibe}}) or else from {{der|en|da|gibbe||jib, jibe}}, related to Swedish {{m|sv|gippa||jib, jibe, jerk, make jump}}. Compare also {{cog|gmh|gempeln||to spring}}, {{cog|sv|guppa||to move up and down}}, {{cog|sv|gumpa||to jump, spring}}. See {{l|en|jump}}.

